diff --git a/libavformat/movenc.c b/libavformat/movenc.c
--- a/libavformat/movenc.c
+++ b/libavformat/movenc.c
Description: Force-enable all audio and data tracks in MOV/MP4 output.

Two changes to mov_write_tkhd_tag():

1. Set track header flags to 0xF for audio and data tracks:
   - track_enabled (0x1)
   - track_in_movie (0x2)
   - track_in_preview (0x4)
   - track_size_is_aspect_ratio (0x8)
   This ensures ALL audio tracks are visible and active in NLEs
   (Avid, Premiere, DaVinci Resolve) rather than some being disabled.

2. Set alternate_group to 0 for all tracks:
   When tracks share a non-zero alternate_group, players treat them
   as mutually exclusive alternatives (only one plays at a time).
   Setting to 0 makes every track independent, which is required
   for multi-track broadcast deliverables.

Use case: ProRes MOV with 8 audio tracks for broadcast delivery
where all tracks must be active and independently addressable.

Applied via: scripts/apply-patches.sh (Step 6)
